---
Invasions are realm-wide defense events against a mythic boss and endless waves.

How invasions start
- Invasions can start only when at least one non-staff player is online.
- The system checks once per invasion tick after cooldown.
- Each check has a 5% chance to start an invasion.
- After an invasion ends (win/loss/cleanup), a cooldown is applied before another can start.

Core objective
- Defend Gertrude in room vnum 1209 (The Temple of Midgaard).
- Kill the invasion boss before Gertrude takes too many invasion hits.
- If the boss dies: defenders win.
- If Gertrude dies (or reaches the explosion failure threshold): defenders lose.

Scaling and spawn behavior
- Boss level is based on the highest online player's pseudo level + 20.
- Regular wave mobs scale from online player pseudo levels.
- Spawn counts scale with player count (more players = more invaders).
- Boss pressure increases over time: while the boss survives, extra mobs are spawned.
- Wave durability/difficulty also rises with prolonged respawns.

Invader behavior
- Non-boss invasion mobs path toward Gertrude every room update tick.
- They are not naturally aggressive, but they march relentlessly.
- They can unlock/open doors while pathing.
- If they reach Gertrude's room, they explode and are removed.
- If an invader cannot path to Gertrude, it crumbles away.

Gertrude pressure system
- Each tick where invaders detonate at Gertrude increments invasion pressure.
- Gertrude issues warning invasion channel messages at 10, 15, and 19 hits.
- At 20 hits, Gertrude falls and the invasion is lost.

Rewards
On invasion success:
- Every online non-staff player receives:
  - 25 quest points
  - 1 invasion point

On killing invasion mobs:
- Killers can receive invasion reward tokens by mob level:
  - Commendation: invader level <= 100
  - Ribbon: invader level 101-149
  - Medal: invader level >= 150
- Boss kills end the invasion and trigger the global success reward.

Tracking your invasion progression
- SCORE displays:
  - Invasion points
  - Invasion rewards (commendations/ribbons/medals) when you have any

Quartermaster and invasion emblems
- A quartermaster NPC can exchange invasion currency for wearable invasion emblems.
- Use LIST near a quartermaster to view emblem tiers/styles and prices.
- Buy syntax: BUY <tier> <style>
- Tiers: common, magic, rare
- Styles: caster, melee, tank

Current emblem costs
- common caster/melee/tank: 1 invasion point + 5 commendations
- magic caster/melee/tank: 10 invasion points + 50 commendations + 5 ribbons
- rare caster/melee/tank: 100 invasion points + 500 commendations + 50 ribbons + 5 medals

Staff control
- Staff can use: iinvasion <start|stop|status|bosses>

Tips
- Focus boss pressure first, but do not ignore marching waves.
- In larger player populations, expect significantly heavier spawn volume.
- Keep routes open when possible; invaders will force doors when needed.
